value.title: Trump will 'have a place in history' for Capitol riot but remains 'most popular figure' in GOP: Graham
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump will "have a place in history" for his role leading up to the riot at the U.S. Capitol last month, but he stills remains the "most popular figure" in the Republican Party, Sen. Lindsey Graham said Sunday.

value.title: Biden says he won't lift sanctions on Iran to bring country back to negotiating table
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said the US will not lift sanctions to get Iran back to the negotiating table, suggesting the measure would only happen if Tehran stops enriching uranium.

value.title: Meadows: Biden administration policies prioritize 'America last'
value.excerpt: President Biden’s record number of executive orders aren’t focused on putting America and the people first, former White House chief of staff Mark Meadows told "Sunday Morning Futures."

value.title: Sen. Rand Paul: Claim Trump incited Capitol riot is 'big lie'
value.excerpt: Hundreds of thousands of more of those high-paying career jobs will also be gone as Joe follows through on his promise and his plan to cancel all oil and gas pipelines and block drilling and exploration in ANWR Alaska,

value.title: GOP senator: 'Very unlikely' Senate votes to convict Trump in impeachment trial
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Pat Toomey of Pennsylvania said Sunday it's "very unlikely" the Senate votes to convict former President Donald Trump in the impeachment trial set to begin Tuesday.

value.title: Biden 'ignoring' federal law with sweeping executive orders, Texas AG Paxton says
value.excerpt: President Biden is 'ignoring' federal law with sweeping executive orders on immigration he has signed since taking office, Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton said Sunday, creating a "huge risk" for his state.

value.title: Sen. Murphy: 'We have a constitutional responsibility' to hold Trump's trial
value.excerpt: Sen. Chris Murphy, D-Conn., argued on Sunday that the Senate has “a constitutional responsibility” to hold the impeachment trial of former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Rand Paul: Kids missing school is 'disaster,' says Biden 'beholden' to teachers unions
value.excerpt: President Biden's hands-off approach to reopening schools amid the coronavirus pandemic is hurting America's children, Sen. Rand Paul, R-Ky., told "Justice with Judge Jeanine" Saturday.

value.title: ‘If this happened in the Soviet Union, you would call it a show trial,’ Cassidy of Trump impeachment trial
value.excerpt: Sen. Bill Cassidy (R-La.) tells Chuck Todd that the House did an incredibly 'poor job' in building a case against President Trump during his second impeachment trial, during an exclusive interview with Meet the Press.

value.title: Majority of Americans say Trump should be convicted, barred from holding federal office in impeachment trial: POLL
value.excerpt: In a new ABC News/Ipsos poll, a majority of Americans support the Senate convicting former President Trump in his second impeachment trial, but the partisan gap persists.

value.title: Ben Sasse's anti-Trump statements draw more Nebraska backlash
value.excerpt: Republican U.S. Sen. Ben Sasse is facing more opposition in his home state of Nebraska for criticizing former President Trump.

value.title: Biden says minimum wage increase looks like it's not 'going to survive' as part of COVID-19 relief package
value.excerpt: "I put it in, but I don't think it's going to survive," Biden said, though Sen. Bernie Sanders still insists including it is a "moral imperative."

value.title: Liz Cheney censured by Wyoming Republican party for voting to impeach Trump
value.excerpt: Cheney, the third ranking member of the House Republican leadership, was censured in a vote Saturday by her state’s Republican party

value.title: Ivanka Trump’s political re-emergence would likely center on criminal justice reform work: report
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump helped to secure pardons and commutations for over 140 in her father’s final days in office, and could champion criminal justice reform in a new foray into politics.

value.title: Biden gives Calif. woman pep talk in weekly address revival
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has given a pep talk to a California woman who was laid off because of the coronavirus pandemic

value.title: Harris flexes power as Senate tiebreaker
value.excerpt: Early Friday morning, Vice President Kamala Harris did something Joe Biden never did in his eight years as vice president -- cast a tie-breaking vote.

value.title: Illinois judge finds Trump hotel in Chicago liable for violating environmental laws
value.excerpt: The hotel has been sucking in millions of gallons of Chicago River water for its air-conditioning systems, without renewing a permit to do so.

value.title: Biden administration to remove Houthis from terrorist list, reversing Trump's decision
value.excerpt: The State Department has informed Congress of its intent to reverse the Trump administration's eleventh-hour decision to designate Yemen's Houthi rebels as a foreign terrorist organization, a State Department official said Friday.

value.title: Transgender Navy SEAL: Biden order 'going to give a lot of other individuals that chance to finally be themselves'
value.excerpt: When Navy SEAL Ashley Nefzger heard rumblings that President Joe Biden could sign an executive order to repeal a Trump-era ban on most transgender Americans joining the military, she was cautiously hopeful.

value.title: Biden says 'no need' for Trump to receive intel briefings: 'What impact does he have?'
value.excerpt: President Biden said he didn’t think his predecessor should receive intelligence briefings, as is standard for former presidents.

value.title: 'People are hurting,' Biden says as jobs report spurs stimulus push
value.excerpt: After weak jobs data showed the U.S. labor market recovery is stalling, President Joe Biden and his economic team on Friday hammered home the same message in meetings, interviews and television appearances: It's time to get more money out to the economy.

value.title: Hunter Biden still ‘working to unwind’ investment in Chinese firm
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden’s son Hunter maintains a holding in a Chinese investment firm, though the White House says he is "working to unwind his investments."

value.title: Pence's plans post-Trump administration take shape
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence's post-Trump administration life is now starting to take shape. He's planning to host a new podcast and will be joining two conservative think tanks. Pence will be launching a podcast with Young America's Foundation,

value.title: Pro-Trump GOP chair steps down in Ohio, may seek Senate seat
value.excerpt: An Ohio Republican linked closely to Donald Trump has stepped down as the party’s chair, a signal of her interest in running for the U.S. Senate seat being left by the GOP’s Rob Portman

value.title: Biden administration likely going back to 'good old days' of Iran nuclear deal: McFarland
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is likely to look to go back to the "good old days" by renegotiating the Iran nuclear deal, former Deputy National Security Advisor K.T. McFarland told "America Reports" Friday.
